# Obsidian MCP Server Development Rules

## Code Style
- Use async/await for all I/O operations
- Follow PEP 8 style guide
- Use type hints for all functions
- Keep functions focused and under 50 lines

## MCP Protocol
- All MCP responses must follow JSON-RPC 2.0 format
- Include proper error handling with JSON-RPC error codes
- Support SSE streaming for responses

## Testing
- Test all Obsidian API integrations
- Verify authentication on protected endpoints
- Test error cases and edge conditions

## Security
- Validate all user inputs
- Prevent path traversal attacks
- Use environment variables for secrets